<div id=3D"div-cee72b2" class=3D"div-c1be943">
<p id=3D"paragraph-c1268bf" class=3D"paragraph-cabd688">How to use the free=
 CPM calculator</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-c232ae5" class=3D"paragraph-c0b53ee">Using GRIN=E2=80=99=
s free CPM Calculator is easy. Simply fill in any two inputs and click =E2=
=80=9Ccalculate=E2=80=9D to reveal the third input box.&nbsp;</p>



<div id=3D"list-c44869d" class=3D"list-cd48ba3"><ul><li><strong>Total cost =
of a campaign:</strong> Be sure to consider all costs associated with your =
campaign, including the cost of products gifted to creators, flat rates pai=
d to creators, etc.</li><li><strong>Cost per 1,000 impressions (CPM):</stro=
ng> CPM is the price you pay for every 1,000 times a piece of creator conte=
nt is displayed to your target audience.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Number of im=
pressions:</strong> Enter the total number of times your content was displa=
yed, regardless of whether anyone clicked it or not.</li></ul></div>
</div>
</div>



<div id=3D"tab-content-2" class=3D"div-c54dfe1 tab-content">
