<div id=3D"div-c5b5a78" class=3D"div-c7eea41">
<p id=3D"paragraph-cd83a63" class=3D"paragraph-cc722fd">CPM definition and =
benchmarks to strive for</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-cecbc2f" class=3D"paragraph-ccf3c72">CPM stands for =E2=
=80=9Ccost per 1,000 impressions.=E2=80=9D It measures how much it costs to=
 show your ad to 1,000 people on social media or other advertising platform=
s. Instead of paying for each view or click, CPM calculates the cost for ev=
ery 1,000 times your ad is displayed, regardless of whether people interact=
 with it or not.</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-c21bef9" class=3D"paragraph-cb9ad25">What is a good CPM?=
</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-c75e4a0" class=3D"paragraph-c966f09">A good CPM will dep=
end on multiple factors, including the size and engagement of your creator=
=E2=80=99s audience, the industry or niche, and your overall campaign goals=
. But as a general guideline, <strong>consider $10 as a benchmark for influ=
encer marketing campaigns</strong>. That means you=E2=80=99re paying $10 or=
 less to reach 1,000 impressions with a creator=E2=80=99s sponsored content=
.</p>
</div>
</div>



<div id=3D"tab-content-3" class=3D"div-c8d618b tab-content">
<div id=3D"div-cc1e2fd" class=3D"div-c7c64e7">
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" id=3D"image-c3d5c95" class=3D"imag=
