fluencer reviewing a VR headset">
</div>



<div id=3D"div-ca66c53" class=3D"div-c1d396a">
<p id=3D"paragraph-c0a3f8c" class=3D"paragraph-c85641f">How to calculate CP=
M</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-cb8c804" class=3D"paragraph-ca7cddd">You can calculate C=
PM by dividing the total cost of a campaign by the number of impressions ge=
nerated, then multiplying the result by 1,000. <br><br><strong>CPM =3D (Tot=
al Cost / Number of Impressions) x 1,000 <br></strong><br>For example, if a=
 campaign costs $500 and generates 100,000 impressions, you would calculate=
 the CPM as:<br><br>CPM =3D ($500 / 100,000) x 1,000 CPM =3D $5 <br>In this=
 case, the CPM is $5, meaning it costs $5 to reach 1,000 impressions.</p>
</div>
</div>



<div id=3D"tab-content-4" class=3D"div-c2d6f9c tab-content">
<div id=3D"div-cda408d" class=3D"div-ca8b6d4">
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" id=3D"image-c1fbc26" class=3D"imag=
e-cd5f1b1 cc-img" src=3D"https://grin.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Who-We-=
Help_7-Biz-Leaders-Loyalists-1.webp" width=3D"1201" height=3D"1201" alt=3D"=
Smiling women sitting on stairs">
</div>



<div id=3D"div-c1a0aff" class=3D"div-cfd799f">
<p id=3D"paragraph-c6713ec" class=3D"paragraph-c27fd6c">How to calculate im=
pressions from CPM</p>



<p id=3D"paragraph-ce18c02" class=3D"paragraph-ce51d71">To calculate impres=
sions from CPM), you need to divide the total cost of the campaign by the C=
PM value, then multiply the result by 1,000. <br><br>The formula for calcul=
ating impressions from CPM is as follows: <br><strong>Impressions =3D (Tota=
l Cost / CPM) x 1,000 <br></strong><br>For example, if the CPM is $5 and th=
e total cost of the campaign is $500, the calculation would be: Impressions=
 =3D ($500 / $5) x 1,000 Impressions =3D 100,000 <br>In this case, the camp=
aign would generate 100,000 impressions.</p>
</div>
</div>



<div id=3D"tab-content-5" class=3D"div-c5475c3 tab-content">
